# So long I've been loving you,
I will never forget you #

1131
01:56:35,300 --> 01:56:40,800
# I lost my beloved without
deserving it #

1132
01:56:41,200 --> 01:56:48,200
# For a bunch of
roses that I denied him #

1133
01:56:48,400 --> 01:56:55,500
# So long I've been loving you,
I will never forget you #

1134
01:56:56,700 --> 01:57:02,500
# I wanted the rose
to be still on the bush #

1135
01:57:02,800 --> 01:57:10,200
# And my sweet beloved
to be still loving me #

1136
01:57:10,800 --> 01:57:17,700
# So long I've been loving you,
I will never forget you #

1137
01:57:18,300 --> 01:57:24,100
# At the clear fountain,
while I was strolling by #

1138
01:57:24,300 --> 01:57:30,800
# I found the water so
nice that I went in to bathe #

1139
01:57:31,600 --> 01:57:38,500
# So long I've been loving you,
I will never forget you #

1140
01:57:38,900 --> 01:57:44,300
# Under an oak tree, I dried myself #

1141
01:57:44,700 --> 01:57:51,000
# On the highest branch, a
nightingale was singing #

1142
01:57:51,600 --> 01:58:01,700
# So long I've been loving you,
I will never forget you #

1143
01:58:12,200 --> 01:58:14,200
It's silly, really.

1144
01:58:14,600 --> 01:58:16,499
They'll die in a week.

1145
01:58:16,500 --> 01:58:18,500
It's hardly worth the cost.

1146
01:58:19,800 --> 01:58:21,099
What do you think?

1147
01:58:21,100 --> 01:58:23,100
I think they're quite nice.

1148
01:58:23,500 --> 01:58:25,500
Really?

1149
01:58:25,900 --> 01:58:27,900
I think you're right.

1150
01:58:29,800 --> 01:58:31,800
Come on.

1151
01:58:33,800 --> 01:58:36,000
We better hurry. Grandfather's waiting.

1152
01:58:40,400 --> 01:58:42,400
Kitty Fane?

1153
01:58:45,200 --> 01:58:47,099
As I live and breathe.

1154
01:58:47,100 --> 01:58:48,999
Hello, Charlie.

1155
01:58:49,000 --> 01:58:51,000
What are you doing in London?

1156
01:58:53,700 --> 01:58:55,700
I know it's been a long time.

1157
01:58:57,200 --> 01:58:59,200
I should have written.

1158
01:59:01,600 --> 01:59:03,700
Who's this fine chap? Hello, young man.

1159
01:59:04,200 --> 01:59:05,199
What's your name?

1160
01:59:05,200 --> 01:59:06,499
Walter.

1161
01:59:06,500 --> 01:59:10,100
Hello, Walter. I'm Charlie Townsend.

1162
01:59:11,600 --> 01:59:12,899
How old are you?

1163
01:59:12,900 --> 01:59:14,499
Five.

1164
01:59:14,500 --> 01:59:17,200
Come on, darling. We should
really press on.

1165
01:59:17,600 --> 01:59:19,600
Yes, of course.

1166
01:59:19,700 --> 01:59:22,700
Well, it's lovely seeing you again.

1167
01:59:26,000 --> 01:59:27,299
Goodbye, Walter.

1168
01:59:27,300 --> 01:59:29,300
Goodbye.

1169
01:59:32,800 --> 01:59:34,800
Kitty!

1170
01:59:35,300 --> 01:59:37,300
I'm going to be in London for
the next 3 weeks. Perhaps we could...

1171
01:59:37,400 --> 01:59:39,400
Goodbye, Mr. Townsend.

1172
01:59:41,000 --> 01:59:43,000
Goodbye, Mrs. Fane.

1173
01:59:46,100 --> 01:59:48,100
Who was that, Mommy?

1174
01:59:48,700 --> 01:59:50,700
No one important, darling.

